# Indicator Source Links

get_canada_data.py
- FRED API: https://fred.stlouisfed.org/
- Bank of Canada Valet API: https://www.bankofcanada.ca/valet/

get_china_data.py
- FRED API: https://fred.stlouisfed.org/
- People’s Bank of China: http://www.pbc.gov.cn/
- OECD: https://data.oecd.org/
- World Bank: https://data.worldbank.org/

get_germany_data.py
- FRED API: https://fred.stlouisfed.org/
- OECD: https://data.oecd.org/
- World Bank: https://data.worldbank.org/

get_japan_data.py
- FRED API: https://fred.stlouisfed.org/
- Bank of Japan: https://www.boj.or.jp/en/statistics/
- OECD: https://data.oecd.org/
- World Bank: https://data.worldbank.org/

get_us_data.py
- FRED API: https://fred.stlouisfed.org/
- OECD: https://data.oecd.org/
- World Bank: https://data.worldbank.org/

calculate_yield_spread.py
- Reads 2‑year and 10‑year government bond yield data from collected CSVs
  and computes the yield spread (10Y – 2Y).
  No external data source – processes files like US-2Y, US-10Y CSVs.